<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">document in connection therewith, Lender shall
not be entitled to receive, collect or apply, as interest on any Obligation,
any amount in excess of the Maximum Amount (the &#147;Excess&#148;).&#160; As used herein, &#147;Maximum Amount&#148; shall mean
the maximum amount of interest which would have accrued if the unpaid principal
amount of the Obligation outstanding from time to time had borne interest each
day at the maximum amount of interest which lender is permitted to charge on
the Obligation under the Usury Laws.&#160; If
Lender ever receives, collects or applies as interest any Excess, such Excess
shall be deemed a partial repayment of principal and treated hereunder as such;
and if principal is paid in full, any remaining Excess shall be paid to
Borrower.&#160; In determining whether or not
the interest paid or payable under any specific contingency exceeds the Maximum
Amount, Borrower and Lender shall, to the maximum extent permitted under the
Usury Laws, (a) characterize any nonprincipal payment as an expense, fee or
premium rather than as interest, (b) exclude voluntary prepayments and the
effect thereof, and (c) amortize, prorate, allocate and spread in equal parts,
the total amount of interest throughout the entire contemplated term of the
Obligation so that the interest rate is uniform throughout the entire term of
the Obligation; provided that if the Obligation is paid and performed in full
prior to the full contemplated term thereof, and if the interest received for
the actual period of existence thereof exceeds the Maximum Amount, Lender shall
refund to Borrower the Excess, and, such event shall not be subject to any
penalties provided by the Usury Laws.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">23.&#160; GOVERNING LAW.</font></b>&#160; THE
INTERPRETATION, CONSTRUCTION AND VALIDITY OF THIS AGREEMENT AND THE NOTE SHALL
BE GOVERNED BY THE LAWS OF THE STATE OF NEW YORK WITHOUT REFERENCE TO CONFLICT
OF LAW PROVISIONS.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">24.&#160; MISCELLANEOUS. </font></b>&#160;(a)
Subject to the limitations herein, this Agreement shall be binding upon and
inure to the benefit of the parties hereto and their respective heirs,
administrators, successors and assigns.&#160;
(b) This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts, which
together shall constitute a single instrument.&#160;
(c) Section and paragraph headings in this Agreement are for convenience
only and have no independent meaning.&#160;
(d) The terms of this Agreement shall be severable and if any term
thereof is declared unconscionable, invalid, illegal or void, in whole or in
part, the decision so holding shall not be construed as impairing the other
terms of this Agreement and this Agreement shall continue in full force and
effect as if such invalid, illegal, void or unconscionable term were not
originally included herein.&#160; (e) All
indemnity obligations of Borrower under this Agreement and all rights, benefits
and protections provided to Lender by warranty disclaimers shall survive the
cancellation, expiration or termination of this Agreement.&#160; (f) Lender shall not be liable to Borrower
for any indirect, consequential or special damages for any reason whatsoever.&#160; (g) This Agreement may be amended, but only
by a written amendment signed by Lender and Borrower.&#160; (h) If this Agreement is signed by more than
one Borrower, each of such Borrowers shall be jointly and severally liable for
payment and performance of all of Borrower&#146;s obligations under this Agreement.
(i) This Agreement represents the final, complete and entire agreement between
the parties hereto, and there are no oral or unwritten agreements or
understandings affecting this Agreement or the Collateral.&#160; (j) Borrower agrees that Lender is not the
agent of any manufacturer or supplier, that no manufacturer or supplier is an
agent of Lender, and that any representation, warranty or agreement made by
manufacturer, supplier or by their employees, sales representatives or agents
shall not be binding on Lender.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">24</font></b>.&#160; <b><font style="font-weight:bold;">GOVERNMENT REGULATION</font></b>.&#160;&#160;
Borrower shall not (a) be or become subject, at any time, to any law,
regulation, or list of any government agency (including, without limitation,
the U.S. Office of Foreign Asset Control list) that prohibits or limits Lender
from making any advance or extension of credit to Borrower or from otherwise
conducting business with Borrower or (b) fail to provide documentary and other
evidence of Borrower&#146;s identity as may be requested by Lender at any time to enable
Lender to verify Borrower&#146;s identity or to comply with any applicable law or
regulation, including, without limitation, Section 326 of the USA Patriot Act
of 2001, 31 U.S.C. Section 5318.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">25</font></b>. <b><font style="font-weight:bold;">USA PATRIOT ACT
NOTIFICATION</font></b>.&#160; The following
notification is provided to Borrower pursuant to Section 326 of the USA Patriot
Act of 2001, 31 U.S.C. Section 5318:</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT
PROCEDURES FOR OPENING A NEW ACCOUNT. To help the government fight the funding
of terrorism and money laundering activities, Federal law requires all
financial institutions to obtain, verify, and record information that
identifies each person or entity that opens an account, including any deposit
account, treasury management account, loan, other extension of credit, or other
financial services product. What this means for Borrower: When Borrower opens
an account, if Borrower is an individual, Lender will ask for Borrower&#146;s name,
tax payer identification number, residential address, date of birth, and other
information that will allow Lender to identify Borrower, and if Borrower is not
an individual, Lender will ask for Borrower&#146;s name, taxpayer identification
number, business address, and other information that will allow Lender to
identify Borrower.&#160; Lender may also ask,
if Borrower is an individual, to see Borrower&#146;s driver&#146;s license or other
identifying documents, and if Borrower is not an individual, to see Borrower&#146;s
legal organizational documents or other identifying documents.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">[The
next page is the signature page.]</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Together with all engines,
propellers, avionics, communication equipment, navigation equipment,
instruments, accessories, attachments, parts, appurtenances, accessions,
furnishings and other equipment attached to, installed in or relating to any of
the foregoing property and all maintenance and service logs and records
relating to the foregoing property.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each engine has 750 or more rated takeoff
horsepower or the equivalent of such horsepower.</font></p>

propellers, avionics, communication equipment, navigation equipment,
instruments, accessories, attachments, parts, appurtenances, accessions,

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each engine has 750 or more rated takeoff
horsepower or the equivalent of such horsepower.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This item of Equipment shall be based at the
following location:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Together with all engines,
propellers, avionics, communication equipment, navigation equipment,
instruments, accessories, attachments, parts, appurtenances, accessions,
furnishings and other equipment attached to, installed in or relating to any of
the foregoing property and all maintenance and service logs and records
relating to the foregoing property.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each engine has 750 or more rated takeoff
horsepower or the equivalent of such horsepower.</font></p>

horsepower or the equivalent of such horsepower.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Together with all engines,
propellers, avionics, communication equipment, navigation equipment,
instruments, accessories, attachments, parts, appurtenances, accessions,
furnishings and other equipment attached to, installed in or relating to any of
the foregoing property and all maintenance and service logs and records
relating to the foregoing property.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each engine has 750 or more rated takeoff
horsepower or the equivalent of such horsepower.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This item of Equipment shall be based at the
following location:</font></p>

instruments, accessories, attachments, parts, appurtenances, accessions,
furnishings and other equipment attached to, installed in or relating to any of
the foregoing property and all maintenance and service logs and records
relating to the foregoing property.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each engine has 750 or more rated takeoff
horsepower or the equivalent of such horsepower.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Together with all engines,
propellers, avionics, communication equipment, navigation equipment,
instruments, accessories, attachments, parts, appurtenances, accessions,
furnishings and other equipment attached to, installed in or relating to any of
the foregoing property and all maintenance and service logs and records
relating to the foregoing property.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each engine has 750 or more rated takeoff
horsepower or the equivalent of such horsepower.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This
item of Equipment shall be based at the following location:</font></p>

County, CO&#160; 81506</font></i></b></h1>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">SCHEDULE&nbsp; 2</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Attached to Loan and Security Agreement for
Loan No.&nbsp;1000122039</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">ADDITIONAL CONDITIONS TO FUNDING THE LOAN*</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Lender shall conduct a satisfactory physical
inspection of the Collateral, at the expense of Borrower, to include
satisfactory review and acceptance of all maintenance and service logs and
reports relating to the Collateral.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Lender shall receive terminations or releases
of liens in a form recordable with the Federal Aviation Administration from all
creditors with a lien on any part of the Collateral as shown in the FAA lien
records.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Lender shall receive UCC-3 terminations
or release of liens in recordable form from all creditors with a lien on any
part of the Collateral as shown in state or local lien records.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Lender shall receive confirmation that all
nine (9)&nbsp;Learjets included in the Collateral are on an approved engine
maintenance program (MSP or JSSI).</p>

  </td>
  <td width="70%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:70.38%;">

  </td>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Dear
Agent:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Chase Equipment Leasing Inc. (&#147;CELI&#148;) (f/k/a
Banc One Leasing Corporation) requires proof of acceptable insurance coverage
before the loan transaction can close.&#160;
The requirements identified below must stay in full effect throughout
the term of the transaction.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The certificate of insurance must be issued
directly to Chase Equipment Leasing Inc. and shall be issued by a company
having an&nbsp;A.M. Best Rating of at least A with a Financial Size Category of
at least VII.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The certificate of insurance must be executed.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The insurance must be primary and any
insurance maintained by CELI or any other loss payee will be in excess and
non-contributory.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Policies must include a Waiver of Subrogation
in favor of &#147;Chase Equipment Leasing Inc., its parent and affiliates,
successors or assigns&#148;.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Policies must include a thirty (30) day prior
written Notice of Cancellation to the Certificate Holder.&#160; Such notice must be directed by certified
mail to: Chase Equipment Leasing Inc., 1111 Polaris Parkway, Suite&nbsp;A3,
Columbus, Ohio 43240, Attn:&#160; Insurance
Dept.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">6.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>PHYSICAL DAMAGE</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">a.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Replacement cost coverage for the equipment
identified on the attached Schedule&nbsp;A-1, which is estimated to be
$15,600,000.00.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">b.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>&#147;Chase Equipment Leasing Inc., its parent and
affiliates, successors or assigns&#148; shall be named as Loss Payee.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">c.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Breach of Warranty in favor &#147;Chase Equipment
Leasing Inc., its parent and affiliates, successors or assigns&#148;.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">d.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>War Risk Endorsement, which shall include
hijacking and terrorism, in favor of &#147;Chase Equipment Leasing Inc., its parent
and affiliates, successors or assigns&#148; for the amount identified in 6a.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">7.</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>The certificate of insurance shall evidence
liability coverage in the minimum amount of $50 million.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Please
immediately send proof of the above insurance requirements <b><font style="font-weight:bold;">VIA
FACSIMILE TRANSMITTAL 614-213-0748</font></b>.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">PLEASE REFERENCE THE COMPLETE LOAN NUMBER AS LISTED BELOW FOR TRACKING
PURPOSES.</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">THANK YOU.</font></b></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">EXHIBIT 4.45</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">BUSINESS PURPOSE PROMISSORY NOTE</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(fixed rate//principal and interest)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Loan Number: <u>1000122039</u></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">

  </td>
  <td width="8%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in .7pt 0in .7pt;width:8.1%;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  &#147;Loan Agreement&#148;) </font></b></p>

  <td width="12%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:12.22%;">

  </td>
  <td width="58%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:58.9%;">

 <tr>
  <td width="9%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:9.48%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  </td>
  <td width="12%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:12.22%;">
  <p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(City)</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="11%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:11.96%;">

  </td>
  <td width="58%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:58.9%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <td width="71" style="border:none;"></td>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For value received, receipt
of which is hereby acknowledged, the undersigned<b><font style="font-weight:bold;"> </font></b>(&#147;Borrower&#148;)
promises to pay to the order of CHASE EQUIPMENT LEASING INC. (f/k/a Banc One
Leasing Corporation) (&#147;Lender&#148;) at its principal office or at such other place
as Lender may designate from time to time in lawful money of the United States
of America, the principal sum of <b><font style="font-weight:bold;">ELEVEN
MILLION and 00/100ths Dollars ($11,000,000.00)</font></b>, or such lesser portion
thereof as may have from time to time been disbursed to, or for the benefit of
Borrower, and as remains unpaid pursuant to the books or records of Lender,
together with interest at the Interest Rate set forth below on the unpaid
balance of principal advanced from the date(s) of disbursement until paid in
full as set forth below.&#160; Principal
sums(s) disbursed and repaid will not be available for redisbursement.&#160; Interest shall be calculated on a 360-day
year basis with each month consisting of 30 days.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Interest Rate: <u>8.12</u>% per annum</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.&#160; The term of this Note consists
of the Interim Term plus the Base Term.&#160;
The Interim Term begins on the Acceptance Date and continues up to the
Commencement Date of the Base Term.&#160; The
Acceptance Date is the date that Lender accepts this Note by initially
disbursing principal hereunder.&#160; If the
Acceptance Date is on or after the first (1st) day of the month and up to the
fifteenth (15th) day of the month, then the Commencement Date shall be the
fifteenth (15th) day of such month; and if the Acceptance Date is on or after
the sixteenth (16th) day of the month and up to the last day of the month, then
the Commencement Date shall be first (1st) day of the month following the
Acceptance Date.&#160; The Base Term begins on
the Commencement Date and continues for the number of months after the
Commencement Date as stated in Section 3 below.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.&#160; If the Acceptance Date is before the
Commencement Date, then on the Commencement Date of the Base Term, Borrower
shall pay one installment of interest only based upon the number of days in the
Interim Term.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3.&#160; During the Base Term, Borrower shall pay
installments of principal and interest in the amounts and on the dates stated
below:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(a)&#160; Base Term: <b><font style="font-weight:bold;">36
Months</font></b></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.25in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(b)</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Amount of each installment payment due during the Base Term (includes
principal and interest):</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:2.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">35 @ $209,871.31 each</font></b></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:2.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1 @</font></b> <b><font style="font-weight:bold;">$5,709,871.31</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(c)&#160; The first installment payment during the Base
Term shall be paid <b><u><font style="font-weight:bold;">one month</font></u></b>
after the Commencement Date and all subsequent installment payments shall be
paid on the same day of <b><u><font style="font-weight:bold;">each month</font></u></b>
thereafter until paid in full.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4.&#160; On or before the date of this Note, Borrower
shall pay a set-up/filing fee in the amount of <b><u><font style="font-weight:bold;">$0.00.</font></u></b></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .3in;text-indent:-.3in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5.&#160; Payments shall be allocated between
principal, interest and fees, if any, in the discretion of Lender.&#160; Except as provided in paragraph 6 below,
Borrower may not prepay the principal sum, in whole or part.&#160; Borrower&#146;s obligation to pay all installment
payments and all other amounts payable under this Note is absolute and unconditional
under any and all circumstances and shall not be affected by any circumstances
of any character including, without limitation,&#160;
(a) any setoff, claim, counterclaim, defense or reduction which Borrower
may have at any time against Lender or any other party for any reason, or (b)
any defect in the condition, design or operation of, any lack of fitness for
use of, any damage to or loss of, or any lack of maintenance or service for any
of the Equipment (as defined in the Loan Agreement).</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .3in;text-indent:-.3in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">6.
Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Note or the Loan Agreement,
Borrower and Lender agree that anytime after the first twelve (12) months of
the Base Term of this Note, so long as no Event of Default has occurred and
continues </font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-indent:0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\JMS\Snagara\05-2037-1\task373357\2037-1-ko.htm',USER='snagarajan',CD='Mar 30 04:10 2005' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-indent:0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .3in;text-indent:0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">under
the Loan Agreement and so long as Borrower gives Lender at least 20 days prior
written notice (the &#147;Notice Period&#148;), Borrower may elect to prepay its
obligations under this Note and the Loan Agreement by paying to Lender on the
installment payment date (a &#147;Payment Date&#148;) following the Notice Period the
total of the following: (a) all accrued installment payments, interest, taxes,
late charges and other amounts then due and payable under this Note and the
Loan Agreement; plus (b) the remaining principal balance payable by Borrower
under this Note as of said Payment Date (hereinafter, the &#147;Principal Balance&#148;);
plus (c) a prepayment premium equal to the product of the applicable Prepayment
Percentage set forth below and the Principal Balance as of the applicable
Payment Date set forth below:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">From month 13 of the Base
Term of this Note through month 24 of the Base Term of this Note, the
Prepayment Percentage is 2.5%.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">From month 25 of the Base
Term of this Note through the maturity date of this Note, the Prepayment
Percentage is 1.5%.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">7.&#160; At any time during the Term of the Note,
Borrower may request that Lender release Lender&#146;s security interest in one or
more of the aircraft that is the &#147;Equipment&#148; as described in the Loan Agreement
(the &#147;Released Aircraft&#148;) and Lender shall consent to such release, but solely
on the terms and conditions set forth below in this paragraph 7 and only if
such terms and conditions are satisfied on or before the release of Lender&#146;s
security interest in the Released Aircraft:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(a) Borrower shall grant
Lender a first and sole security interest in a &#147;Substitute Aircraft&#148; as
described in this paragraph 7;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(b) no
event of default shall have occurred and be continuing under the Loan Agreement
or this Note;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(c) Borrower gives Lender at
least 30 days prior written notice of the requested release of the Released
Aircraft and such notice shall include a complete description of the Substitute
Aircraft (including make, model and serial number of the airframe, engines and,
if applicable, propellers), maintenance records for the Substitute Aircraft,
and the purchase price paid or to be paid by Borrower for the Substitute
Aircraft;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(d) in
Lender&#146;s sole judgment, the Substitute Aircraft has an orderly liquidation
value no less than 141.8% of the outstanding principal balance of the
unamortized Equipment Cost of the Released Aircraft;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(e) Borrower shall have
acquired good title to the Substitute Aircraft at Borrower&#146;s sole expense, the
Substitute Aircraft shall be free and clear of any Liens (except for Lender&#146;s
security interest), and Borrower shall furnish Lender with copies of the
acquisition invoices and FAA Bill of Sale for the Substitute Aircraft;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(f) Borrower shall execute
and deliver to Lender such documents as Lender may request including, without
limitation, an amendment to the Loan Agreement or a new security agreement
similar to the Loan Agreement;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(g) Borrower shall pay any
and all out-of-pocket costs and expenses of Lender in connection with the
foregoing, including, without limitation, the fees and expenses of outside
counsel, including outside aviation counsel, to Lender who shall render an
opinion of counsel which confirms the foregoing statements about title to and
Liens on the Substitute Aircraft; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .3in;text-indent:-.3in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(h)
Borrower shall not substitute for more than seven (7) aircraft during the term
of the Loan Agreement.&#160; Borrower may
substitute for either Released Aircraft or Substitute Aircraft.&#160; If Borrower substitutes for a Substitute
Aircraft, for purposes of this Section, the Substitute Aircraft shall be considered
a Released Aircraft; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(i) in
consideration of Lender&#146;s consent to the Substitute Aircraft transaction,
Borrower shall pay Lender a non-refundable fee $1,000.00.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .3in;text-indent:-.3in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">8.&#160; This Note is entitled to the benefits, and is
subject to the terms and requirements of, the Loan Agreement executed by
Borrower and Lender, which Loan Agreement, among other things, (a) provides for
the making of the loan evidenced hereby, and (b) provides for events of
default, acceleration and other remedies.&#160;
Borrower waives presentment, demand, protest or notice of any kind in
connection with this Note.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

</font></div>

<body lang="EN-US">

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit
4.46</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">[AirNet
Systems, Inc. Letterhead]</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">March
31, 2005</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Securities and Exchange Commission</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">450 Fifth Street, N.W.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Washington, D.C.&#160; 20549</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Re:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">AirNet Systems,
Inc. &#151; Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K for the fiscal year ended December
31, 2004</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.5in;text-indent:-.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Ladies and Gentlemen:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">AirNet Systems, Inc., an
Ohio corporation (&#147;AirNet&#148;), is today filing its Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K
for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2004 (the &#147;Form&nbsp;10-K&#148;).</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Pursuant to the provisions
of Item 601(b)(4)(iii) of Regulation&nbsp;S-K, AirNet hereby agrees to
furnish to the Commission, upon request, copies of those instruments and
agreements defining the rights of holders of long-term debt of AirNet and of
holders of long-term debt of AirNet&#146;s consolidated subsidiaries, which are not
being filed as exhibits to the Form&nbsp;10-K.&#160; Such long-term
debt does not exceed 10% of the total assets of AirNet and it subsidiaries on a
consolidated basis.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 12.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Very truly yours,</font></p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">
 <tr>
  <td width="100%" colspan="2" valign="top" style="padding:0in .7pt 0in .7pt;width:100.0%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">AIRNET SYSTEMS, INC.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>

  <td width="21%" valign="top" style="border:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in .7pt 0in .7pt;width:21.14%;">

  </td>
  <td width="78%" valign="top" style="padding:0in .7pt 0in .7pt;width:78.86%;">

<DOCUMENT>
<TYPE>EX-10.26
<SEQUENCE>10
<FILENAME>a05-2037_1ex10d26.htm
<DESCRIPTION>EX-10.26
<TEXT>
<html>

<head>





</head>

<body lang="EN-US" link="blue" vlink="purple">

<div>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">EXHIBIT 10.26</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">SUMMARY
OF COMPENSATION</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">FOR
DIRECTORS OF</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">AIRNET
SYSTEMS, INC.</font></u></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Directors of AirNet
Systems, Inc. (&#147;AirNet&#148;) who are not officers or employees of AirNet
(&#147;Non-Employee Directors&#148;) are paid fees for their services as members of the
Board of Directors and as members of Board committees.&#160; The quarterly fee paid in 2004 and to be paid
in 2005 for serving as a Non-Employee Director was and remains $6,000.&#160; The fee for attending each meeting of the
full Board of Directors in person was $2,000 in 2004 and continues to be the
same amount in 2005.&#160; The fee for
attending telephonic meetings of the full Board was $2,000 in 2004.&#160; At a meeting held on December 22, 2004, the Non-Employee
Directors discussed, and on March 9, 2005, the Board of Directors affirmed
that, effective for the telephonic meetings of the full Board held after
January 1, 2005, the fee would be $1,000 for each meeting attended.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The fee for Audit
Committee members was $2,000 per meeting attended in 2004, with the Chair of
the Audit Committee receiving an additional $1,000 per meeting attended.&#160; The fee for Compensation Committee members
and Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee members was $1,000 per
meeting attended in 2004, with the Chair of each of those Committees receiving an
additional $2,000 for each meeting of the Committee attended.&#160; At a meeting held on December 22, 2004, the Non-Employee
Directors discussed, and on March 9, 2005, the Board of Directors affirmed that
the fees for attending in person Committee meetings held after January 1, 2005
would remain the same as they had been in 2004; however, the fees for attending
telephonic meetings of each Committee held after January 1, 2005 would be
one-half (50%) of the amount of the fees for attending a meeting of the particular
Committee in person.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As the lead director of
AirNet, James E. Riddle received an additional quarterly fee of $6,000 for
service in that capacity in 2004 and continues to receive that quarterly fee in
2005.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Non-Employee
Directors meet without management present in connection with each of the regularly
scheduled meeting of the full Board and receive no meeting fees for attending
such meetings.&#160; To the extent the
Non-Employee Directors determine to meet by telephone or in person other than
in connection with a regularly scheduled Board Meeting they will receive $2,000
per meeting attended in person and $1,000 per telephonic meeting. AirNet&#146;s
Non-Employee Directors are reimbursed for out-of-pocket expenses incurred in
connection with their service as directors, including travel expenses.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As an officer and
employee of AirNet, Joel E. Biggerstaff receives no additional compensation for
serving as a director of AirNet.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Effective
May 27, 1998, AirNet established the AirNet Systems, Inc. Director Deferred
Compensation Plan (the &#147;Director Deferred Plan&#148;).&#160; The Director Deferred Plan as in effect on
March&nbsp;30, 2005 has previously been filed as Exhibit&nbsp;10.7 to AirNet&#146;s
Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10-K for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31,
2003.&#160; Voluntary participation in the
Director Deferred Plan enables a Non-Employee Director of AirNet to defer all
or a part of his director&#146;s fees, including federal income tax thereon.&#160; Such deferred fees may be credited to
(1)&nbsp;a cash account where the funds will earn interest at the rate
prescribed in the Director Deferred Plan, or (2)&nbsp;a stock account where the
funds will be converted into a common share equivalent (deter&#173;mined by dividing
the amount to be allocated to the Non-Employee Director&#146;s stock account by the
fair market value of AirNet&#146;s common shares when the credit to the stock
account is made).&#160; In his deferral
election, a Non-Employee Director will elect whether distribution of the amount
in his account(s) under the Director Deferred Plan is to be made in a single lump
sum payment or in equal annual installments payable over a period of not more
than ten years.&#160; Distributions will
commence within 30&nbsp;days of the earlier of (a)&nbsp;the date specified by a
Non-Employee Director at the time a deferral election is made or (b)&nbsp;the
date the Non-Employee Director ceases to so serve.&#160; Cash accounts will be distributed in the form
of cash and stock accounts will be distributed in the form of common shares or
cash, as selected by AirNet.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Non-Employee
Directors have been automatically granted options to purchase AirNet common
shares in accordance with the terms of the AirNet Systems, Inc. Amended and
Restated 1996 Incentive Stock Plan (the &#147;1996 Plan&#148;).&#160; The 1996 Plan as in effect on March&nbsp;30,
2005 has previously been filed as Exhibit&nbsp;10.1 to AirNet&#146;s Annual Report
on Form&nbsp;10-K for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2003.&#160; On March&nbsp;7, 1997, each individual then
serving as a Non-Employee Director was automatically granted an immediately
exercisable option to purchase 2,000 AirNet common shares with an exercise
price equal to the fair market value of the common shares on the grant
date.&#160; On August 19, 1998, each
individual then serving as a Non-Employee Director was automatically granted an
option to purchase 20,000 AirNet common shares with an exercise price equal to
the fair market value of the common shares on the grant date.&#160; Each option granted on August 19, 1998 became
exercisable with respect to 20% of the common shares on each of the grant date
and the first, second, third and fourth anniversaries of the grant date.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Pursuant
to the 1996 Plan, each individual newly-elected or appointed as a Non-Employee
Director from August 19, 1998 until June&nbsp;4, 2004 was automatically granted
an option to purchase 20,000 AirNet common shares effective on the date of his
election or appointment to the Board.&#160; In
addition, on the first business day of each of the 2002, 2003 and 2004 fiscal
years of AirNet, each individual who was then serving as a Non-Employee
Director and had served for at least one full one-year term as a Non-Employee
Director, was automatically granted an option to purchase 4,000 AirNet common
shares.&#160; All of these options were
granted with an exercise price per share equal to the fair market value of the
common shares on the grant date.&#160; In
addition, all of these options have vested and are to vest and become
exercisable with respect to 20% of the common shares on each of the grant date
and the first, second, third and fourth anniversaries of the grant date.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each
option granted to a Non-Employee Director under the 1996 Plan since August 18,
1999, will become fully exercisable if the Non-Employee Director retires from
service as an AirNet director, becomes totally disabled or dies, or if AirNet
merges with another entity and AirNet is not the survivor in the merger, or if
all or substantially all of AirNet&#146;s assets or stock is acquired by another
entity.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each
option granted to a Non-Employee Director under the 1996 Plan has a ten-year
term.&#160; If a Non-Employee Director ceases
to be a member of the Board, his vested options may be exercised for a period
of three months (12 months in the case of a Non-Employee Director who becomes
disabled or dies) after the date his service ends, subject in each case to the
stated terms of the options.&#160; However, a
Non-Employee Director who ceases to be a director after having been convicted
of, or pled guilty or nolo contendere to, a felony immediately forfeits his
options.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\JMS\sshanka\05-2037-1\task377622\2037-1-ks.htm',USER='sesankaran',CD='Mar 31 07:12 2005' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Following the approval of the AirNet Systems, Inc. 2004 Stock Incentive
Plan (the &#147;2004 Plan&#148;) by the shareholders of AirNet at the 2004 Annual Meeting
of Shareholders held on June&nbsp;4, 2004, no further option grants have been
or will be made to the Non-Employee Directors under the 1996 Plan.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The 2004 Plan as in effect on March&nbsp;30, 2005 has been filed as
Exhibit&nbsp;10.1 to AirNet&#146;s Quarterly Report on Form&nbsp;10-Q for the
quarterly period ended June&nbsp;30, 2004.&#160;
Under the 2004 Plan, each
individual newly-elected or appointed as a Non-Employee Director after
June&nbsp;4, 2004 is to be granted an option to purchase 20,000 AirNet common
shares effective on the date of his election or appointment to the Board.&#160; In addition, on the first business day of
each fiscal year of AirNet, each individual who is then serving as a
Non-Employee Director and has served for at least one full one-year term as a
Non-Employee Director, is to be automatically granted an option to purchase
4,000 AirNet common shares.&#160; However,
each of the individuals serving as a Non-Employee Director on January&nbsp;3,
2005 (the first business day of the fiscal year ending December 31, 2005),
determined not to accept the option to purchase 4,000 AirNet common shares
which would have been automatically granted to him on that date.</font></p>

<p align="left" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:left;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Any
options automatically granted in the future to Non-Employee Directors under the
2004 Plan will vest and become exercisable as to 20% of the common shares on
each of the grant date and the first, second, third and fourth anniversaries of
the grant date and will have an exercise price per share equal to the fair market
value of the underlying common shares on the grant date.&#160; Each such option will become fully
exercisable if the Non-Employee Director retires from service as an AirNet
director after having served at least one full one-year term, becomes totally
disabled or dies or if AirNet undergoes a merger or consolidation or
reclassification of the common shares or the exchange of the common shares for
the securities of another entity (other than a subsidiary of AirNet) that has
acquired AirNet&#146;s assets or which is in control of an entity that has acquired
AirNet&#146;s assets.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:37.05pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each
option automatically granted in the future to a Non-Employee Director under the
2004 Plan will have a ten-year term.&#160; If
a Non-Employee Director ceases to be a member of the Board, his vested options
may be exercised for a period of three months (24 months in the case of a
Non-Employee Director who becomes disabled, dies or retires) after the date his
service ends, subject in each case to the stated terms of the options.&#160; However, if a Non-Employee Director&#146;s service
as a director is terminated for cause, he will immediately forfeit his options.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

</div>

<DOCUMENT>
<TYPE>EX-10.27
<SEQUENCE>11
<FILENAME>a05-2037_1ex10d27.htm
<DESCRIPTION>EX-10.27
<TEXT>
<html>

<head>





</head>

<body lang="EN-US">

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">EXHIBIT 10.27</font></b></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">SUMMARY OF AIRNET SYSTEMS, INC. 2005 INCENTIVE COMPENSATION PLAN</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On February 2, 2005, the
Board of Directors of AirNet, upon the recommendation of the Compensation
Committee, adopted the 2005 Incentive Compensation Plan (the &#147;Incentive Plan&#148;).&#160; The Compensation Committee and the Board of
Directors subsequently approved clarifications and modifications to the
Incentive Plan on March 8, 2005 and March 29, 2005.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The purpose of the Incentive
Plan is to promote the following goals of AirNet for the fiscal year ending on
December 31, 2005 (&#147;Fiscal 2005&#148;) by providing incentive compensation to
certain employees of AirNet and its subsidiaries:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in 6.0pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#149;</font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>Exceeding budgeted pre-tax income;</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in 6.0pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#149;</font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>Reducing fixed costs;</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in 6.0pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#149;</font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>Creating and executing contingency plans for
changes in AirNet&#146;s Bank business;</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in 6.0pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#149;</font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>Refining AirNet&#146;s business plan for its
Express and Jetride businesses to more quickly and profitably diversify AirNet;</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in 6.0pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#149;</font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>Developing AirNet&#146;s leadership team; and</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#149;</font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>Meeting high priority deadlines related to compliance with the
Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 and other key projects.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Participants in the Incentive
Plan include AirNet&#146;s executive officers, including Joel E. Biggerstaff
(Chairman of the Board, Chief Executive Officer and President), Gary W.
Qualmann (Chief Financial Officer, Treasurer and Secretary), Larry M.
Glasscock, Jr. (Senior Vice President, Express Services), Jeffery B. Harris
(Senior Vice President, Bank Services), Robert L. Austin (Senior Vice
President, Jetride Services), Craig A. Leach (Vice President, Information
Systems) and Wynn D. Peterson (Vice President, Strategic Planning and Analysis)
and certain department managers and department directors.&#160; At the start of Fiscal 2005, there were 45
participants in the Incentive Plan.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Payments under the Incentive
Plan are based on a combination of AirNet&#146;s pre-tax income for Fiscal 2005,
operating performance of AirNet&#146;s various business components, and the
achievement of personal goals assigned to each participant. The Compensation
Committee approves personal goals for each of the executive officers and
reviews the personal goals established by senior management for other
participants.&#160; The personal goals
approved by the Compensation Committee for each of the executive officers
relate to specific business objectives related to general business operations
(e.g., regulatory compliance, expense reductions, etc.) and each business
component (e.g., execution of specific contracts with customers and vendors,
cost reductions, service improvements, etc.).</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">No incentive compensation
will be paid under the Incentive Plan unless AirNet achieves a designated
threshold level of pre-tax income for Fiscal 2005.&#160; Once the designated threshold level is
achieved, incentive compensation payments will increase at predetermined pre-tax
income levels until the maximum compensation payout of $1.9 million is reached
at approximately 200% of Fiscal 2004 pre-tax income, determined without regard
to the Fiscal 2004 impairment charges related to property and equipment and
goodwill.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Once the overall amount of
incentive compensation is determined based upon AirNet&#146;s pre-tax income,
incentive compensation will be allocated to Bank, Express, Jetride and
corporate based upon pre-established targets.&#160;
Incentive compensation will then be allocated to the participants most
closely involved in managing each of those business areas based upon each
participant&#146;s base salary.&#160; Finally,
participants must achieve their pre-established personal goals to achieve their
maximum incentive compensation payment.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The maximum percentage of
annual base salary that each of the executive officers may receive as incentive
compensation under the Incentive Plan is as follows: Joel E. Biggerstaff, 100%;
Gary W. Qualmann, Larry M. Glasscock, Jr., Jeffrey B. Harris, and Robert L.
Austin, 75%; and Craig A. Leach and Wynn D. Peterson, 50%.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;">Except for payments to
executive officers, payments under the Incentive Plan will be paid in quarterly
payments commencing with the second quarter of Fiscal 2005 based upon AirNet&#146;s
year to date financial performance.&#160;
Payments of incentive compensation to executive officers will be made in
the first quarter of Fiscal 2006 based upon AirNet&#146;s performance for Fiscal
2005.&#160; In order to receive </font>payment</font>, a participant must be actively employed by
AirNet or one of its subsidiaries at the time payment is made.&#160; New
employees who qualify for the Incentive Plan will be eligible to participate on
the first day of the calendar quarter following their date of hire.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Compensation Committee
may amend, modify or terminate the Incentive Plan at any time.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

</div>

<div>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">EXHIBIT 24</font></b></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">POWER OF ATTORNEY</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">KNOW ALL MEN BY THESE PRESENTS, that the undersigned
officer and director of AirNet Systems, Inc., an Ohio corporation, which is
about to file with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Washington, D.C.,
under the provisions of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, the
Annual Report on Form 10-K for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2004, hereby
constitutes and appoints Gary W. Qualmann as his true and lawful
attorney-in-fact and agent, with full power of substitution and resubstitution,
for him and in his name, place and stead, in any and all capacities, to sign
both the Annual Report on Form 10-K and any and all amendments and documents
related thereto, and to file the same, with any and all exhibits, financial statements
and financial statement schedules related thereto, and other documents in
connection therewith, with the Securities and Exchange Commission and the New
York Stock Exchange, and grants unto said attorney-in-fact and agent, and
substitute or substitutes, full power and authority to do and perform each and
every act and thing requisite and necessary to be done in and about the
premises, as fully to all intents and purposes as he might or could do in
person and hereby ratifies and confirms all things that the said
attorney-in-fact and agent, or his substitute or substitutes, may lawfully do
or cause to be done by virtue hereof.</font></p>

this 30<sup>th</sup> day of March, 2005.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">POWER OF ATTORNEY</font></p>

Exchange, and grants unto said attorney-in-fact and agent, and substitute or

substitute or substitutes, may lawfully do or cause to be done by virtue

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Gary W. Qualmann</font></p>
  </td>

<div>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">POWER OF ATTORNEY</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">KNOW ALL MEN BY THESE PRESENTS, that the undersigned
officer of AirNet Systems, Inc., an Ohio corporation, which is about to file
with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Washington, D.C., under the provisions
of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, the Annual Report on Form
10-K for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2004, hereby constitutes and
appoints Joel E. Biggerstaff and Gary W. Qualmann as her true and lawful
attorneys-in-fact and agents, with full power of substitution and
resubstitution, for her and in her name, place and stead, in any and all
capacities, to sign both the Annual Report on Form 10-K and any and all
amendments and documents related thereto, and to file the same, with any and
all exhibits, financial statements and financial statement schedules related
thereto, and other documents in connection therewith, with the Securities and
Exchange Commission and the New York Stock Exchange, and grants unto each of
said attorneys-in-fact and agents, and substitute or substitutes, full power
and authority to do and perform each and every act and thing requisite and
necessary to be done in and about the premises, as fully to all intents and
purposes as she might or could do in person and hereby ratifies and confirms
all things that each of the said attorneys-in-fact and agents, or substitute or
substitutes, may lawfully do or cause to be done by virtue hereof.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the undersigned has hereunto set her hand as of
this 30<sup>th</sup> day of March, 2005.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
